svg.title: 472_a2_final
svg.text: Canadas rate of refugee resettlement has increased to the second highest globally, resettling an average of 2,909 refugees per month, second only to Germany.
Since November 2015, Canada has resettled over 30,000 Syrian Refugees: more than tenfold than during the previous five years of the Syrian Civil War.
From 2011 to 2015, Canadas role in the Syrian Refugee Crisis was limited. As other countries increased their intake of refugees, Canadas rate of refugee resettlement hardly budged.
The per capita concentrations of resettled refugees are not in urban centres, but in less populat-ed regions
data sources: Eurostat, Government of Canada, UNHCR, US State Dept
